BT
/F1 10 Tf
50 800 Td
13 TL
(Extraction Comparator Calculation Methodology) Tj
T*
(Input: manual triples are compared with LLM triples.) Tj
T*
(Manual triple shape: source -> [relation] -> target.) Tj
T*
(LLM row shape: source, source_type, relation, target, target_type.) Tj
T*
(Text is normalised: lowercase, remove punctuation, split into words.) Tj
T*
(Word similarity uses Jaccard = shared words / total unique words.) Tj
T*
(Source score compares manual source with LLM source.) Tj
T*
(Relation score compares manual relation with LLM relation.) Tj
T*
(Target score compares manual target with LLM target.) Tj
T*
(Triple score = source score x 0.4 + relation score x 0.2 + target score x 0.4.) Tj
T*
(For each manual row, the system chooses the LLM row with the highest triple score.) Tj
T*
(Threshold example: 60 percent means match cutoff is 0.60.) Tj
T*
(Partial cutoff = threshold x 0.5. With 60 percent threshold, partial cutoff is 30 percent.) Tj
T*
(If score >= threshold: Match.) Tj
T*
(If score >= partial cutoff and below threshold: Partial.) Tj
T*
(If score is below partial cutoff: Miss.) Tj
T*
(Partial matches receive half credit.) Tj
T*
(TP = matches + partials x 0.5.) Tj
T*
(FP = max of LLM count minus TP, or 0.) Tj
T*
(FN = misses + partials x 0.5.) Tj
T*
(Precision = TP / TP plus FP.) Tj
T*
(Recall = TP / TP plus FN.) Tj
T*
(F1 = 2 x precision x recall / precision plus recall.) Tj
T*
(Accuracy = TP / manual count.) Tj
T*
(Hallucinations = rounded FP.) Tj
T*
(Hallucination rate = FP / LLM count.) Tj
T*
(Best saved result ranks by F1, accuracy, precision, recall, then lower hallucination rate.) Tj
T*
(In simple words: it rewards correct matches, gives partial credit, and penalises extra LLM triples.) Tj
ET
